//Optimization level for TpetraKernels computational kernels: a
// nonnegative integer.  Higher levels result in better performance
// that is more uniform for corner cases, but increase build time
// and library size.  The default value is 1, which should give
// performance within ten percent of optimal on most platforms,
// for most problems.

//Whether Kokkos allows use of lambdas at the outer level of parallel
// dispatch (that is, as the argument to an outer parallel_for,
// parallel_reduce, or parallel_scan).  This requires C++11.  It
// also does not currently work with public releases of CUDA. 
// As a result, even if C++11 is enabled, this will be OFF by default
// if CUDA is enabled.  If this option is ON, the macro KOKKOS_HAVE_CXX11_DISPATCH_LAMBDA
// will be defined.  For compatibility with Kokkos' Makefile build
// system, it is also possible to define that macro on the command

//List of semi-colon separated paths to append to the compile invocations
// to find the headers for the TPL HDF5.  This is the final variable
// that is used in the build commands.  The user variable HDF5_INCLUDE_DIRS
// is used to look for the given headers first but is just a suggestion.
// This variable, however, is the final value and will not be touched.
TPL_HDF5_INCLUDE_DIRS:PATH=/projects/vera/gcc-4.8.3/tpls/opt/hdf5-1.8.10/include

//List of semi-colon separated full paths to the libraries for
// the TPL HDF5.  This is the final variable that is used in the
// link commands.  The user variable HDF5_LIBRARY_DIRS is used
// to look for the know library names but but is just a suggestion.
// This variable, however, is the final value and will not be touched.
TPL_HDF5_LIBRARIES:FILEPATH=/projects/vera/gcc-4.8.3/tpls/opt/hdf5-1.8.10/lib/libhdf5_hl.so;/projects/vera/gcc-4.8.3/tpls/opt/hdf5-1.8.10/lib/libhdf5_cpp.so;/projects/vera/gcc-4.8.3/tpls/opt/hdf5-1.8.10/lib/libhdf5_fortran.so;/projects/vera/gcc-4.8.3/tpls/opt/hdf5-1.8.10/lib/libhdf5.so;/projects/vera/gcc-4.8.3/tpls/opt/zlib-1.2.7/lib/libz.so

//Set by default in vera-tpls-std.cmake
TPL_INSTALL_DIR:PATH=/projects/vera/gcc-4.8.3/tpls/opt

//Use the Murmur hash function in Tpetra::Map for global-to-local
// index lookups, rather than the default hash function.  Murmur

//Whether to enable automatic run-time registration of LinearSolverFactory
// in downstream packages.  All packages that intend to register
// a LinearSolverFactory at run time, before main() starts, must
// respect this option.  Its default value is VERA_ENABLE_EXPLICIT_INSTANTIATION
// = ON, because if explicit template instantiation (ETI) is OFF,
// the automatic registration option increases build time.  The
// LinearSolver and LinearSolverFactory interfaces remain even
// if this option is OFF, but in that case, users must do manual
// registration for all solver packages which they (or solvers)
// might like to use.
Trilinos_ENABLE_LINEAR_SOLVER_FACTORY_REGISTRATION:BOOL=ON

//Location where assorted examples will be installed.  If given
// as a relative path, it will be relative to .  If given as an
// absolute path, it will used as such.  Default is 'example'

//Enable the installation of executables provided by the VERA packages.
VERA_INSTALL_EXECUTABLES:BOOL=ON

//Location where the headers will be installed.  If given as a
// relative path, it will be relative to .  If given as an absolute
// path, it will used as such.  Default is 'include'
VERA_INSTALL_INCLUDE_DIR:PATH=include

//Set by default in vera-core-enables.disables.cmake
VERA_INSTALL_LIBRARIES_AND_HEADERS:BOOL=OFF

//Location where the libraries will be installed.  If given as
// a relative path, it will be relative to .  If given as an absolute
